The paper discusses a CAD-based system for robot programming and introduces sensory feedback for force and torque sensing in unstructured environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for CAD modeling and fuzzy-PI reasoning (cs.AI) for force control. The paper also discusses the calibration process and the use of sensory feedback to increase tolerance to positioning errors, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach through experiments, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
